# TESAIoT firmware and Bitstream (external workspaces)

**Host BS2 spec + TypeScript:** this repo — **`extension/docs/BS2_PROTOCOL_INDEX.md`**, **`extension/src/bitstream2/`**.

Firmware on-wire implementation is **not** vendored in Bitstream-Studio. When the task mentions protocol fields, encoders, or MCU behavior, check:

| Role | Path |
|------|------|
| **Main firmware** | `D:\CODE\2026\TESAIoT_PSoC_Edge_Workspace\TESAIoT_Firmware` |
| **Library** | `D:\CODE\2026\TESAIoT_PSoC_Edge_Workspace\TESAIoT_Library` |
| **Bitstream module (firmware authoritative)** | `D:\CODE\2026\TESAIoT_PSoC_Edge_Workspace\TESAIoT_Library\CM55\modules\bitstream` |
| **Host wire spec (canonical)** | `extension/docs/BITSTREAM_BS_FRAMED_PROTOCOL_SPEC.md` |
| **Host encode/decode** | `extension/src/bitstream2/` |

**bitstream-simulator** — separate VSIX; see **`bitstream-simulator-app-path.mdc`**.

After wire changes: **`.cursor/rules/bs2-protocol-change.mdc`** (spec → host code → tests → firmware → sim).

Communication: **Thai and/or English** only.
